The paper deals with list decoding of algebraic-geometric codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of linear-algebraic techniques and subspace designs suggests a connection to coding theory (cs.CC) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the error-correction radius and alphabet size, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.SI).
